            "ratingValue": "5",
            "bestRating": "5",
            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "I got kids to this great school because I was looking for a school and teachers who taught true history and native Marathi and Bhartey culture to the kids.\n\nI got kids out of a famous Missionary school as they brainwashed kids to a level that they stopped participating in Ganpati pujan, Deepavli etc. at home. All at home faced a lot of stress as kids revolted and abused elders. Alcohol & beef became normal for them as Missnaries brainwashed them while no one in family drinks or even smokes.\n\nSanskriti school improved their scores also and they managed to win at National level. Gradually they came out of communal hatred that missionaries embedded in older Christian school.\n\nSaved on tution fee too but with Bahgwan's aashirwad Money was not an issue. Kids are more friendly and social than before. Now they mingle and play with everyone without any sort of discrimination in heart.\n\nOverall health has also improved. Teachers are very involved here. So, tution outside school is not needed. Kids self study at home with little help from parents or teachers easily available online outside school hours.\n\nBest kart is that Sanskriti school teaches a very healthy competition, without forcing rat race for 99% scores.",
          "publisher": {
            "@type": "Organization",
            "name": "Yellow Slate"
          }
        },
